direction: down
vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}
title: |md
  # Hand-Written vs Auto-Vectorized: When Each Wins
| {near: top-center}
grid-columns: 4
grid-gap: 0
classes: {
  header: {
    style: {
      fill: "#2E3440"
      font-color: "#ECEFF4"
      bold: true
      font-size: 18
    }
  }
  pattern: {
    style: {
      fill: "#3B4252"
      font-color: "#ECEFF4"
      font-size: 14
    }
  }
  cell: {
    style: {
      fill: "#434C5E"
      font-color: "#ECEFF4"
      font-size: 13
    }
  }
  win_hand: {
    style: {
      fill: "#A3BE8C"
      font-color: "#2E3440"
      bold: true
    }
  }
  win_auto: {
    style: {
      fill: "#81A1C1"
      font-color: "#2E3440"
      bold: true
    }
  }
  tie: {
    style: {
      fill: "#EBCB8B"
      font-color: "#2E3440"
      bold: true
    }
  }
}
h1: "Code Pattern" {class: header}
h2: "Hand-Written SIMD" {class: header}
h3: "Auto-Vectorized" {class: header}
h4: "Winner" {class: header}
p1_name: "Aligned Arrays\n(simple arithmetic)" {class: pattern}
p1_hand: "SSE: mulps/addps\n4 floats/cycle" {class: cell}
p1_auto: "AVX: vmulps/vaddps\n8 floats/cycle" {class: cell}
p1_winner: "AUTO\n(wider vectors)" {class: win_auto}
p2_name: "Unaligned Input\n(prologue handling)" {class: pattern}
p2_hand: "Scalar prologue\n+ aligned loop" {class: cell}
p2_auto: "vmovups (unaligned)\nno penalty modern CPU" {class: cell}
p2_winner: "TIE\n(same perf)" {class: tie}
p3_name: "Complex Control Flow\n(conditionals in loop)" {class: pattern}
p3_hand: "Branch-free SIMD\nmask + blend" {class: cell}
p3_auto: "NOT VECTORIZED\ncannot prove safety" {class: cell}
p3_winner: "HAND-WRITTEN\n(3-4x faster)" {class: win_hand}
p4_name: "Horizontal Reduction\n(sum of products)" {class: pattern}
p4_hand: "shuffle+add\n~2 cycle latency" {class: cell}
p4_auto: "vhaddps\n3-5 cycle latency" {class: cell}
p4_winner: "HAND-WRITTEN\n(10-15% faster)" {class: win_hand}
p5_name: "Page-Boundary Safety\n(strlen/memchr)" {class: pattern}
p5_hand: "Aligned-from-below\n+ masking" {class: cell}
p5_auto: "NOT VECTORIZED\ncannot prove safety" {class: cell}
p5_winner: "HAND-WRITTEN\n(only safe option)" {class: win_hand}
p6_name: "Pointer Aliasing\n(unknown overlap)" {class: pattern}
p6_hand: "Manual restrict\nor careful ordering" {class: cell}
p6_auto: "NOT VECTORIZED\nwithout restrict hint" {class: cell}
p6_winner: "HAND-WRITTEN\n(if no restrict)" {class: win_hand}
p7_name: "Specialized Instructions\n(pcmpistri, streaming)" {class: pattern}
p7_hand: "Single instruction\noptimal for task" {class: cell}
p7_auto: "NEVER GENERATED\ncompiler unaware" {class: cell}
p7_winner: "HAND-WRITTEN\n(2-3x faster)" {class: win_hand}
p8_name: "Memory Copy Pattern\n(memcpy-like)" {class: pattern}
p8_hand: "SSE2 stores\n16 bytes/iteration" {class: cell}
p8_auto: "Calls libc memcpy\nAVX-512 optimized" {class: cell}
p8_winner: "AUTO\n(libc wins)" {class: win_auto}
legend_container: "" {
  direction: right
  grid-columns: 3
  grid-gap: 8
  style.stroke: transparent
  style.fill: transparent
  near: bottom-center
  legend_title: "Legend" {
    style: {
      fill: "#2E3440"
      font-color: "#ECEFF4"
      bold: true
    }
  }
  legend_title2: "" {style.opacity: 0}
  legend_title3: "" {style.opacity: 0}
  l1: "HAND-WRITTEN wins" {class: win_hand}
  l2: "AUTO wins" {class: win_auto}
  l3: "TIE" {class: tie}
}
summary: |md
  **Key Insight**: Hand-written SIMD wins when the compiler cannot *prove* safety
  (aliasing, page boundaries) or when specialized instructions exist that the
  compiler never generates. Auto-vectorization wins for simple patterns where
  the compiler can use wider vectors (AVX vs SSE) or call optimized libc.
| {
  near: bottom-center
  width: 700
}